article.description: — Marquise Kennedy came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Loyola of Chicago to a 65-58 win over Bradley on Monday night.
article.headline: Kennedy carries Loyola of Chicago over Bradley 65-58
article.linkText: Kennedy carries Loyola of Chicago over Bradley 65-58
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- — Marquise Kennedy came off the bench to score 18 points to carry Loyola of Chicago to a 65-58 win over Bradley on Monday night. Keith Clemons had 15 points for Loyola of Chicago (13-3, 8-1 Missouri Valley Conference), which earned its sixth straight win. Cameron Krutwig scored seven points but it was enough for him to reach 1,605 points, tied for ninth on the school's career list. Terry Nolan Jr. had 17 points for the Braves (9-7, 3-4). Elijah Childs added 12 points and seven rebounds. Rienk Mast had 11 rebounds. The Rambler defeated Bradley 69-56 on Sunday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
